  {
    "name": "Forward Deployed Security Engineer - US Government",
    "company_name": "palantir",
    "location": "Washington, D.C.",
    "remote": "Unknown",
    "location_lat": 38.9072,
    "location_lon": -77.0369,
    "description": "A World-Changing Company\n \nPalantir builds the world’s leading software for data-driven decisions and operations. By bringing the right data to the people who need it, our platforms empower our partners to develop lifesaving drugs, forecast supply chain disruptions, locate missing children, and more.\n\n\nThe Role\n \nOur team members are subject matter experts in both cybersecurity and US Government policy. We’re excited about generating creative solutions to ambiguous security requirements. Our mission is deploying software in support of our customers' most critical needs as quickly as possible while upholding the government's trust. We achieve this through close consultation with stakeholders and direct ownership of the Authorization to Operate (ATO) process.\n \nAs a Forward Deployed Security Engineer, you support a variety of projects which draw from your wide spectrum of technical experience. You are resourceful, collaborative, and take initiative to improve our processes over time. Most importantly, you are passionate about taking on new challenges and finding innovative ways to support critical missions.\n",
    "type": "Full-time",
    "source": "Lever",
    "source_url": "https://jobs.lever.co/palantir/22053072-4c22-49c4-8299-28e107ceeb98",
