  {
    "name": "Hacking for Health - UK Summer Bootcamp",
    "company_name": "palantir",
    "location": "London, United Kingdom",
    "remote": "Unknown",
    "location_lat": 51.50853,
    "location_lon": -0.12574,
    "description": "Hack to prevent a global pandemic and explore the possibilities of a career in tech at Palantir!\n\nWe are now accepting applications for our Summer 2026 bootcamp aimed at students finishing their A Level or equivalent studies in the summer of 2027. Apply before Friday 19th June.\n\nA potential pandemic looms as lesser-known diseases threaten global health. Determined to avert disaster, the Global Pandemic Prevention Initiative (GPPI) is racing to immunise large populations against these emerging threats. How can they ensure adequate vaccine stock, manage distribution costs, and prioritise the right diseases to vaccinate against?\n\nThat's where you come in. Over four days at Palantir, you will use your problem-solving and data skills to devise a solution to this notional scenario. Armed with cutting-edge technology, and helped by our own engineers, you will develop a solution to a problem that has challenged countries across the globe.\n\nThe Solving Problems with Data Summer Bootcamp is a four-day insight into the world of tech. You’ll get a crash course in the fundamentals of solving problems with data, where we’ll teach you how to break down complex real world problems and build data-driven solutions using Palantir Foundry. \n\nYou’ll gain a deeper understanding of the career opportunities available in technology, as well as introductions to skills that you can take forward into your studies and career, such as working with data, Python, TypeScript, and using AI to solve real-world problems.\n\nIn addition to hands-on technical sessions, you’ll participate in workshops with our Ethics, Privacy and Civil Liberties (PCL), and Information Security teams, covering ethics in tech, how technology can be used to preserve privacy and civil liberties, and cybersecurity fundamentals.\n\nYou’ll work collaboratively with your fellow bootcampers on challenging, motivating problems; developing your skills, and broadening your perspective on the possibilities of careers in tech.\n\nYou’ll also find that our internal community is full of people who are excited to meet you, build community with you, and support your growth! You’ll have a breadth of opportunities to learn about the different technical roles at Palantir and connect with Palantirians to learn more about their unique journeys into tech.\n\nThis program is open to students finishing their A Level or equivalent studies in the summer of 2027. We especially encourage students from communities that are historically underrepresented in STEM to apply.\n",
    "type": "Scholarship",
    "source": "Lever",
    "source_url": "https://jobs.lever.co/palantir/54530b3f-7446-4600-aef3-bfeb47101830",
    "posted": "2022-05-13T20:30:10.315Z",
    "impact_number": 0,
    "audit_number": 0,
    "audit_text": "",
    "tags": [
      "Scholarship"
    ],
    "ai_summary": "",
    "ai_red_flag_summary": "",
    "ai_score": 0,
    "ai_red_flag_score": 0,
    "ai_impact_summary": "",
    "ai_impact_score": 0
  },
  {
    "name": "Incident Management Engineer",
    "company_name": "palantir",
    "location": "London, United Kingdom",
    "remote": "Unknown",
    "location_lat": 51.50853,
    "location_lon": -0.12574,
    "description": "A World-Changing Company\n \nPalantir builds the world’s leading software for data-driven decisions and operations. By bringing the right data to the people who need it, our platforms empower our partners to develop lifesaving drugs, forecast supply chain disruptions, locate missing children, and more.\n\n\nThe Role\n \nIncident Management Engineers (IMEs) are the driving forces of stability across Palantir’s products. IMEs help to ensure Palantir fixes critical issues immediately. When something goes wrong, IMEs are the first to respond and are responsible for triaging, troubleshooting, and coordinating the resolution of the issue.\n \nYou’ll be a member of a centralized team responsible for managing the most critical outages. You are an excellent communicator, collaborator, and troubleshooter and can use both of these skills in fast-paced and high-stakes environments. You are able to parse technical details quickly and know when to ask for help when you need it.\n \nWhatever the issue is, you are ensuring it gets resolved at a high bar as quickly and seamlessly as possible.\n",
    "type": "Full-time",
    "source": "Lever",
    "source_url": "https://jobs.lever.co/palantir/0dd51d8f-aa78-49f9-ae39-e3b2daa082d1",
    "posted": "2023-09-14T11:55:19.167Z",
    "impact_number": 0,
    "audit_number": 0,
    "audit_text": "",
    "tags": [
      "Product Support"
    ],
